  "prompt": "When and how did Ambrose Bierce die?",
  "response": "Ambrose Bierce, an acclaimed American writer known for his sardonic wit and works like \"An Occurrence at Owl Creek Bridge,\" disappeared under mysterious circumstances in 1914. At the time of his disappearance, Bierce was traveling through Mexico during the tumultuous period of the Mexican Revolution. He had ventured there, reportedly with the intent of joining the fighting or to cover the conflict as a journalist.\n\nOn July 26, 1914, Bierce set out from the city of Chihuahua with a group of other Americans and a Mexican scout. They were last seen heading towards the Sierra Madre mountains. After that, no definitive accounts of his fate emerged. Various theories have been proposed, including that he may have been killed in the fighting, fallen victim to local bandits, or succumbed to the harsh conditions of the region. However, none of these theories have been substantiated, and Bierce's ultimate fate remains one of literary history's enduring mysteries.",
